author: jorton
msg: Remove clutter.  CHANGES should be readable by USERS.
- SVN revision numbers are not relevant to users. Mention them in SVN
- Fixes for compiler warnings are not relevant to users unless they caused bugs.
- Bug reporters need no credit in CHANGES -- thank them in bugzilla, on
mailing lists, and in SVN changelogs as appropriate.
- The mod_ssl change did not fix a bug, per list discussion.

author: woonsan
msg: APA-17: Clean ups for reverse proxy components.
I thought it was possible to provide generic sso credentials retrieval mechanism between different PAs. However, it is not possible or requires nasty app dependencies.
So, I just cleaned up the components of apa-webcontent. So, a PA should include library and reverse proxy component inside itself and set sso creds information. I will add this in j2-admin later.
